13:55.752 --> 13:56.918
We were the same.

13:56.920 --> 13:59.420
We couldn't keep our hands
off each other.

13:59.422 --> 14:03.550
Now we just spend every night
doom-scrolling our life away,

14:03.552 --> 14:07.637
And watching a squirrel surf
on the back of an alligator.

14:07.639 --> 14:10.265
Marge! Trashing our marriage
is something that should

14:10.267 --> 14:12.475
Only be done in the privacy
of our home.

14:12.477 --> 14:15.478
And that's our romance
for the ages.

14:15.480 --> 14:19.607
It began with a wild night
in a mini-golf windmill,

14:19.609 --> 14:22.735
And now... [blows raspberry]

14:22.737 --> 14:24.237
How can you say that?!

14:24.239 --> 14:26.197
This is the worst thing
that's ever happened

14:26.199 --> 14:28.700
In the beheading room
of this castle.

14:32.747 --> 14:36.833
Bart, I want to thank you
for bringing me back to maisie.

14:36.835 --> 14:39.127
I've never been so happy.

14:39.129 --> 14:41.129
You know, I think I get it.

14:41.131 --> 14:43.256
Good lad.
That's why I'm giving you

14:43.258 --> 14:45.842
A very important role
in the wedding.

14:45.844 --> 14:48.678
You're going to lead the dance.

14:48.680 --> 14:50.847
Ooh, a spikey american.

14:50.849 --> 14:52.599
[country music plays]

14:54.144 --> 14:58.396
No! Men don't let men down!

14:58.398 --> 14:59.564
[straining]

15:02.319 --> 15:03.693
Our cake.

15:03.695 --> 15:06.988
Now what will you shove
in my gob?

15:06.990 --> 15:09.198
[sobbing]

15:10.744 --> 15:13.536
You wee bastard.

15:13.538 --> 15:15.496
You ruined my wedding.

15:15.498 --> 15:16.539
Good.

15:16.541 --> 15:18.249
That's the only friend

15:18.251 --> 15:19.542
That you made in america?

15:19.544 --> 15:20.585
Aye.

15:24.966 --> 15:27.884
Oh, my head.
Homie, what do you take

15:27.886 --> 15:30.720
For a hangover? Huh?

15:31.973 --> 15:33.431
Oh, fine, be that way.

15:33.433 --> 15:36.434
For once, I'm the one
who spoke truth while drunk.

15:36.436 --> 15:40.897
Oh-oh. Running away
from a fight, huh?!

15:40.899 --> 15:43.566
Well, I'm still mad at you!

15:43.568 --> 15:45.193
Well, I'm still mad at you!

15:45.195 --> 15:48.071
You told everyone that
I don't care about romance,

15:48.073 --> 15:50.949
And now they think
homer simpson is vanilla

15:50.951 --> 15:52.283
In the sack!

15:52.285 --> 15:55.662
[echoing]
homer simpson is vanilla
in the sack!

15:55.664 --> 15:57.080
Vanilla in the sack!

15:57.082 --> 15:58.706
Vanilla
in the sack!

15:58.708 --> 16:00.375
Vanilla in the sack!

16:00.377 --> 16:02.460
Bad at sex!

16:05.298 --> 16:08.091
I can't believe I ever
looked up to that guy.

16:08.093 --> 16:09.759
Stupid willie.

16:09.761 --> 16:12.095
[man cackling]

16:12.097 --> 16:13.846
Stupid willie.

16:13.848 --> 16:16.474
That nobody thinks
he can be a macweldon?

16:16.476 --> 16:18.977
Ha! All he's good for
is his nose.

16:18.979 --> 16:21.646
Once they're married,
willie will sniff out

16:21.648 --> 16:24.440
A mother lode of good peat.

16:24.442 --> 16:26.150
And then he's out!

16:26.152 --> 16:27.860
And then maisie can find
a proper husband,

16:27.862 --> 16:29.779
Not some floor-waxing
puke-mopper.

16:29.781 --> 16:31.406
[sinister laughter]

16:31.408 --> 16:34.117
This whole thing was a setup
to use willie?

16:34.119 --> 16:36.411
That girl doesn't even love him?

16:36.413 --> 16:39.330
Why would you do that
to my friend?

16:39.332 --> 16:42.000
Wee sleekit cowerin'
timerous beasties

16:42.002 --> 16:46.963
Shouldn't stick their nebs
in other people's bizzo.

16:46.965 --> 16:50.008
I have no idea
what you just said.

16:50.010 --> 16:51.592
B-but I get the context.

16:51.594 --> 16:53.469
[both grunt]

16:53.471 --> 16:54.429
Let me out!

16:54.431 --> 16:56.597
Oh, no, you're staying
right here

16:56.599 --> 17:00.435
With your only entertainment,
this cribbage board.

17:00.437 --> 17:03.229
[laughs]

17:04.607 --> 17:07.233
Hey, where are the pegs?

17:07.235 --> 17:09.902
Oh, they're in this
little drawer.

17:09.904 --> 17:12.989
[organ playing]

17:15.660 --> 17:18.536
[marge]<i> homer would never get</i>
<i> how sweet this is.</i>

17:18.538 --> 17:22.373
<i> How'd I wind up with the most</i>
<i> unromantic man on earth?</i>

17:22.375 --> 17:24.167
[phone chimes]

17:24.169 --> 17:27.253
<i> Why is he texting me</i>
<i> during a wedding?</i>

17:28.673 --> 17:30.089
<i> Hmm?</i>

17:33.553 --> 17:35.428
[laughing]

17:35.430 --> 17:38.765
They shouldn't be together,
but they are.

17:38.767 --> 17:40.433
[gasps]

17:40.435 --> 17:42.268
Oh...

17:43.480 --> 17:44.729
[panting]

17:44.731 --> 17:46.064
[gasps]

17:47.567 --> 17:48.941
Homer!

17:48.943 --> 17:50.443
Marge!

17:50.445 --> 17:54.072
Did you get my
gorilla-dolphin video?

17:54.074 --> 17:57.784
It was so unlikely,
just like us.

17:57.786 --> 18:00.203
That's why I sent it to you!

18:00.205 --> 18:02.705
I'm sorry I trashed our marriage

18:02.707 --> 18:04.707
In a rehearsal dinner toast.

18:04.709 --> 18:09.003
I'm sorry I was such a downer
about this destination wedding.

18:09.005 --> 18:11.589
I should have just pretended
to go along with it,

18:11.591 --> 18:14.884
Like I do with everything else
in our marriage.

18:14.886 --> 18:17.178
♪

18:19.432 --> 18:21.557
I don't care if our
romance began

18:21.559 --> 18:24.352
When we did it
on a mini-golf course.

18:24.354 --> 18:26.104
It's still epic.

18:26.106 --> 18:28.815
How epic would it be
if we did it on

18:28.817 --> 18:32.443
The best golf course
in the world?

18:32.445 --> 18:35.905
You are so romantic.

18:35.907 --> 18:39.325
Fore... Play.

18:39.327 --> 18:41.369
[both moaning]

18:44.207 --> 18:45.998
I gotta get out of here
and warn willie

18:46.000 --> 18:48.501
That girl's just marrying him
for his nose.

18:48.503 --> 18:49.585
[groans]

18:53.508 --> 18:56.634
Birdseed bags,
soap with willie's face on it,

18:56.636 --> 18:57.885
Sleep masks.

18:57.887 --> 18:59.470
Aha.

18:59.472 --> 19:03.850
I, groundskeeper willie,
take you, booze-maker maisie...

19:03.852 --> 19:04.934
